RIYADH: Saudi Arabia has supported almost 1 million people throughout the Muslim world with charitable aid during Ramadan. The King Salman Humanitarian Aid and Relief Center distributed 330 food baskets in the cities of Koplik and Debar in Albania, benefiting 330 needy families. The center also distributed 400 Ramadan food baskets in the historic city of Weda in the Atlantic governorate and the city of Banti in the Golin governorate in Benin, benefiting 2,400 people. It aims to distribute 2,400 food baskets in a number of Benin cities, benefiting 14,400 people. KSrelief also distributed 905 baskets in the Punjab province of Pakistan, benefiting 6,335 people, and 1,000 baskets in Bangladesh, benefiting 5,000 people. The Saudi Ramadan “Eta’am” initiative aims to distribute 156,993 food baskets weighing 8,430 tons in 19 countries, benefiting more than 900,000 people during Ramadan. The initiative is part of relief and humanitarian projects being implemented by the Kingdom, represented by KSrelief, in many developing countries.